  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit3_Proximal_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit3_Proximal_L
  partName: Forepaw Digit3 Proximal Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left forepaw digit three proximal phalanx is the first bone of the third
    digit located between the metacarpal and middle phalanx within the canine forepaw.
    This structure supports controlled toe movement and contributes significantly
    to balance and weight-bearing during locomotion.
  - Attached tendons and ligaments enable flexion, extension, and stabilization of
    the digit while maintaining proper paw mechanics. The third digit is particularly
    important for supporting body weight during walking, running, and jumping activities.
